<br>
We were buffed, pulling the last few giants when the monk pulling shouted &quot;Who Aggroed Vindi!?&quot;<br>
<br>
Vindi came, we were engaged with a couple other giants and the CH rotation for the MT wasn't started properly so he started reaping players like a combine through a  wheat field. (Typical uber mob HERE flailing went on, clerics camping, people running around scenario  =)<br>
<br>
We all were trying to figure out what happened and why Vindi came ahead of schedule. Initially we thought it was an AE bard song that caused the problem, but after looking at the last place the monk FD'd, he was well out of the radius of the Bardsong. There was also some discussion as to what happened to our pets and some claims that the pets charged ahead.<br>
<br>
I spoke with a friend a bit later who has done Vindi a couple times, he told me that 2 of the giants that are with Vindi are actually coded as his Pets--  he told me that our problem was that because those giants were essentially pets, our* pets had aggro on Vindi. When he came in range of their aggro radius, they went berzerk and charged ahead.<br>
<br>
Anyone confirm or deny this? I'm just looking for some clarificaiton.  =)<br>
<br>
Thanks muchly!<br>
<br>
